The <Wallet /> component enables users to connect their Smart Wallets and display identity information, such as Basenames, avatars, and ETH balances. For example:tsx

import { Wallet, ConnectWallet, WalletDropdown, WalletDropdownDisconnect, Identity, Avatar, Name, Address, EthBalance } from '@coinbase/onchainkit';

export default function Home() {
  return (
    <Wallet>
      <ConnectWallet>
        <Avatar className="h-6 w-6" />
        <Name />
      </ConnectWallet>
      <WalletDropdown>
        <Identity className="px-4 pt-3 pb-2" hasCopyAddressOnClick>
          <Avatar />
          <Name />
          <Address />
          <EthBalance />
        </Identity>
        <WalletDropdownDisconnect />
      </WalletDropdown>
    </Wallet>
  );
}

This code creates a wallet connection interface that allows users to sign in with their email, create a wallet, and perform Web3 actions without needing MetaMask.

